Package FOMS.process_manager

Class DisplayOrder

  • java.lang.Object
    • FOMS.process_manager.DisplayOrder
  • public abstract class DisplayOrder
extends java.lang.Object
    The DisplayOrder abstract class provides static methods to display orders from a file. This class can be used to show all orders, orders specific to a branch, or the details of a single order.
    Since:
    2024-04-24

    • Method Detail

      • displayOrders

        public static void displayOrders()
        Displays all orders from the file. Each order is printed using its toString method.

      • displayOrders

        public static void displayOrders​(java.lang.String branch)
        Displays orders related to a specific branch from the file. It filters orders by the branch associated with each order's menu items.
        Parameters:
        branch - The name of the branch to filter the orders by.

      • viewOrderDetails

        public static void viewOrderDetails​(java.lang.String orderId)
        Displays the details of a single order identified by its order ID. If the order is found, its details are printed; otherwise, a message indicating the order was not found is printed.
        Parameters:
        orderId - The ID of the order to display.
